The paper describes a Prolog-embedded environment for automated reasoning on the basis of first-order logic, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of automated reasoning and various reasoners to support this. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely sub-category as the paper focuses on first-order logic and methods for Craig interpolation and second-order quantifier elimination. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible sub-category as the paper describes a formula macro system and the use of Prolog as a first-order prover. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the creation of documents that intersperse macro definitions, reasoner invocations, and LaTeX-formatted natural language text. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly discuss machine learning, but the use of automated reasoning and reasoners could potentially be applied in machine learning contexts.
